most of our ecosystems.</i>

6
00:01:00.792 --> 00:01:02.875
<i>The world's leading
research laboratories</i>

7
00:01:02.917 --> 00:01:05.875
<i>have been trying to find a way
to stop this deadly pathogen,</i>

8
00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.708
<i>but so far their efforts
have been unsuccessful.</i>

9
00:01:08.750 --> 00:01:10.041
<i>The latest research shows</i>

10
00:01:10.083 --> 00:01:12.625
<i>that people who consume food
infected with the virus</i>

11
00:01:12.667 --> 00:01:15.125
<i>develop severe
autoimmune diseases.</i>

12
00:01:15.167 --> 00:01:15.833
<i>In addition,</i>

13
00:01:15.875 --> 00:01:17.666
<i>the loss of plant life
has contributed</i>

14
00:01:17.708 --> 00:01:20.041
<i>to the concentration of oxygen
in the atmosphere</i>

15
00:01:20.083 --> 00:01:22.250
<i>to decrease to 18%,</i>

16
00:01:22.292 --> 00:01:23.833
<i>the lowest on record.</i>

17
00:01:24.125 --> 00:01:25.958
<i>The rapidly disappearing forests</i>

18
00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.500
<i>cannot recycle
enough carbon dioxide</i>

19
00:01:28.542 --> 00:01:31.125
<i>to maintain this level
for much longer.</i>

20
00:01:31.833 --> 00:01:34.041
<i>These atmospheric
changes have caused</i>

21
00:01:34.083 --> 00:01:37.000
<i>an increase in natural disasters
around the globe.</i>

22
00:01:37.125 --> 00:01:40.083
<i>As oxygen levels
drop below 10%,</i>

23
00:01:40.125 --> 00:01:42.166
<i>people will begin to suffocate.</i>

24
00:01:42.208 --> 00:01:44.833
<i>Our beautiful planet
Earth is doomed.</i>

25
00:01:44.875 --> 00:01:47.541
<i>But humanity still
has a chance of survival.</i>

26
00:01:47.583 --> 00:01:49.791
<i>And their best hope
is Project Gemini,</i>

27
00:01:49.833 --> 00:01:51.958
<i>developed by Dr. Steven Ross.</i>

28
00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:54.083
<i>The project centers
around an archeological find</i>

29
00:01:54.125 --> 00:01:57.416
<i>discovered eight years ago
by a group of palaeontologists</i>

30
00:01:57.458 --> 00:02:00.750
<i>who found two unique objects
of extraterrestrial origin.</i>

31
00:02:01.083 --> 00:02:02.625
<i>The artefacts were estimated</i>

32
00:02:02.667 --> 00:02:05.167
<i>to be more than
4 billion years old.</i>

33
00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:08.458
<i>Steven Hawking once said</i>

34
00:02:09.167 --> 00:02:12.417
<i>that if humans are
to survive long-term,</i>

35
00:02:13.042 --> 00:02:15.125
<i>we must find a way
to get off planet Earth.</i>

36
00:02:15.708 --> 00:02:17.708
<i>He was optimistic
about our chances,</i>

37
00:02:18.167 --> 00:02:21.375
<i>and in fact,
it turns out he was right.</i>

38
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:24.083
These unique devices
that we found

39
